               <head>Sunnī-Shīʿī polemics, 6 items (a-f)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111616 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104277 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2012000503">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on jurisprudence and Sunnī-Shīʿī relations assembled from various sources. Volume not dated; item a dated (mid Ṣafar 1231/January 1816). Scribal nastaʿlīq; Arabic passages overlined in red, but occasionally transcribed in red. Annotations in margins; cropped. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Folios bound; cropped, distinct water stains, wormhole. Condition poor.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic</textLang>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068454" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_236-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="66v">ff. 1r-66v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 236(a), ff. 1r-66v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled jurisprudential treatise on the furūʿ-i dīn ascribed at the end to 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100168182471.0x000001 viaf_12155208" role="aut">Mullā Aḥmad al-Muḥibb ibn Muḥammad ibn Mīkāʾīl Ardbīlī Az̲arbāyjānī</persName>(d. 993/1585), known as 
                <persName key="viaf_12155208" role="aut">Muqaddas Ardabīlī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 66v): completed mid Ṣafar 1231/January 1816.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_12155208">Mullā Aḥmad Ardbīlī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_12155208">ملّا احمد اردبيلى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_236-item2">
                     <locus from="67r" to="88v">ff. 67r-88v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 236(b), ff. 67r-88v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled polemic treatise commenting on passages from the 
                <title key="work_23042">Qurʾān</title>adduced as proofs of Shīʿah doctrine, ascribed at the beginning to 
                <persName key="viaf_12155208" role="aut">Mullā Aḥmad al-Muḥibb ibn Muḥammad ibn Mīkāʾīl Ardbīlī Az̲arbāyjānī</persName>(d. 993/1585), known as 
                <persName key="viaf_12155208" role="aut">Muqaddas Ardabīlī</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_12155208">Mullā Aḥmad Ardbīlī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_12155208">ملّا احمد اردبيلى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_236-item3">
                     <locus from="88v" to="91v">ff. 88v-91v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 236(c), ff. 88v-91v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled excerpt on Sunnī-Shīʿī relations described in the rubricated heading as a letter of 
                <placeName>Māvarāʾ al-Nahr</placeName>scholars in reply to the scholars of Iran, reproduced in the work 
                <title key="work_23043">Tūzuk-i Taymūrī</title>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_236-item4">
                     <locus from="91v" to="99v">ff. 91v-99v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 236(d), ff. 91v-99v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled excerpt on Sunnī-Shīʿī relations described in the rubricated heading as the reply of 
                <persName key="person_f8114" role="aut">Mullā Muḥammad Khādim</persName>, one of the scholars of Iran, addressed to the scholars of 
                <placeName>Māvarāʾ al-Nahr</placeName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The source is not specified (see Delhi Persian item c).</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8114">Mullā Muḥammad Khādim</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_236-item5">
                     <locus from="101r" to="116v">ff. 101r-116v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 236(e), ff. 101r-116v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled excerpt on the 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>described in the rubricated heading as being a selection from an unspecified commentary.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_236-item6">
                     <locus from="116v" to="123v">ff. 116v-123v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 236(f), ff. 116v-123v.</p>
                        <p>Untitled excerpt on the 
                <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>’s companions partial toward Shīʿah beliefs according to a report from the library of the Ethiopian ruler, 
                <persName key="viaf_55721119" role="oth">Najāshī</persName>or 
                <persName key="viaf_55721119" role="oth">Negus</persName>, described in the rubricated heading as copied from the majmūʿah or anthology of 
                <persName key="person_f8115" role="ant">Āqā ʿAlī Khān</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
